#  CLEANING: Filter the data AND create a fresh copy

base_data = base_data[base_data['Age'] >= 0].copy() 


# Group the Age data
# Example labels that would match the 20-year bins:
labels = ['[1-20]', '[21-40]', '[41-60]', '[61-80]', '[81-100]', '[101-120]'] 

base_data['Age_group'] = pd.cut(
    base_data['Age'], 
    range(1, 130, 20), 
    right=False, 
    labels=labels
)

In[32]:
def uniplot(df,col,title,hue =None):
    
    sns.set_style('whitegrid')
    sns.set_context('talk')
    plt.rcParams["axes.labelsize"] = 20
    plt.rcParams['axes.titlesize'] = 22
    plt.rcParams['axes.titlepad'] = 30
    
    
    temp = pd.Series(data = hue)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    width = len(df[col].unique()) + 7 + 4*len(temp.unique())
    fig.set_size_inches(width , 8)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.yscale('log')
    plt.title(title)
    ax = sns.countplot(data = df, x= col, order=df[col].value_counts().index,hue = hue,palette='bright')    
    plt.show()
